  "prompt": "My Instagram account with 8.5k followers just got hacked into. I've spent the the last hour looking up ways to hack it and trying to get it back and nothing's working. How can I get it back?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that your Instagram account has been hacked. Here are steps you can take to try to recover your account:\n\n1. **Use Instagram's Account Recovery:** \n   - Go to the Instagram login page, tap on \"Forgot password?\" or \"Need more help?\" and follow the prompts. You can enter your email address, username, or phone number linked to your account.\n   - Follow any instructions sent to your email or phone to reset your password.\n\n2. **Check Your Email:** \n   - Look for any emails from Instagram regarding changes to your account. If you see a message that someone changed your email address and you didn\u2019t do that, you can revert that change using the link in the email.\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - If you cannot recover your account with the previous steps, go back to the Instagram login page and select \"Need more help?\" Follow the instructions and fill out the form to request assistance. You may need to provide information to verify your identity.\n\n4. **Secure Your Email Account:**\n   - Ensure that your email associated with your Instagram account is secure. Change its password and enable two-factor authentication (2FA) if you haven\u2019t done so already.\n\n5. **Report to Instagram:**\n   - If you still can\u2019t recover your account, report your account as hacked. Visit the Instagram Help Center, and look for the section on hacked accounts. Follow the instructions provided.\n\n6. **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) for Future Prevention:**\n   - Once you regain access to your account, enable 2FA to enhance security.\n\n7. **Check for Other Compromises:**\n   - After you regain access, check your account for any unauthorized changes and secure it by changing your password again.\n\nIf you find that these steps are not working, stay persistent in contacting Instagram's support. Recovery may take time, so be patient.",
